#Text=Post Private Videos on YouTube on PC or Mac
#Text=This wikiHow teaches you how to post private videos to YouTube on PC or Mac .
#Text=When you post a private video on YouTube , it does not appear in any search results , or on your channel .
#Text=Comments are not allowed , and only those you share the video with can view the video .
#Text=You can select to upload the video as private on the same web page you upload videos from .
#Text=Steps
#Text=Uploading a Private Video
#Text=Go to https://www.youtube.com in a web browser .
#Text=You can use any web browser or your choice on PC or Mac .
#Text=If you are not already signed into YouTube , click Sign In in the upper-right corner and sign in with the email address and password associated with your YouTube/Google account .
#Text=Click on your profile picture in the upper right corner of the screen .
#Text=Select YouTube Studio ( beta ) from the drop down menu .
#Text=Click .
#Text=You should see this button in the middle of the screen .
#Text=Click the drop-down menu that says .
#Text=It 's below the upload icon in the center of the screen .
#Text=This drop-down menu allows you to select different privacy options for the video you are about to upload .
#Text=By default , videos you upload are set to Public .
#Text=Select .
#Text=It 's the third option in the drop-down menu .
#Text=This sets the uploaded video to Private .
#Text=This means that only people you invite to view the video can view it .
#Text=Click .
#Text=It 's the icon with an arrow pointing up .
#Text=It 's above the drop-down menu .
#Text=This opens a file browser you can use to browse for video files on your computer .
#Text=You can also drag and drop video files to the upload icon .
#Text=Select a video and click .
#Text=Use the file browser to navigate to the video you want to upload .
#Text=When you find it , click on it and then click Open in the lower-right corner to begin uploading it to YouTube .
#Text=This takes you to another screen that informs you of the processing progress .
#Text=You can also edit the details of the video while it is processing .
#Text=Type a name for the video ( optional ) .
#Text=YouTube automatically names new videos after the file name .
#Text=If you want to change the video title , delete the file name in the first box and type your own name for the video .
#Text=Type a description for the video ( optional ) .
#Text=If you wish to add a description of the video , type it in the large box labeled description .
#Text=Click ( Optional ) .
#Text=If you want to share the video with specific users , click Share below the drop-down menu that says " Private " on the right .
#Text=This displays a pop-up allows you to share the video with users .
#Text=Type the email addresses of users and click .
#Text=If you are sharing the video with specific users , type the email address associated with their YouTube account .
#Text=Then click the blue button that says Ok .
#Text=You can only share a private video with users that have a YouTube account .
#Text=Click .
#Text=This option is available once the video is finished processing .
#Text=It 's the blue button in the upper-right corner .
#Text=This uploads the video as private .
#Text=Only you and other people you share the video with can view the video .
#Text=Sharing a Private Video
#Text=Go to https://www.youtube.com in a web browser .
#Text=You can use any web browser or your choice on PC or Mac .
#Text=If you are not already signed into YouTube , click Sign In in the upper-right corner and sign in with the email address and password associated with your YouTube/Google account .
#Text=Click your profile icon .
#Text=Your profile icon is the image you selected for your Google account .
#Text=It 's in the upper-right corner of the screen .
#Text=This displays your profile menu .
#Text=If you have not selected a profile picture for your Google account , your profile displays a colored circle with your initial .
#Text=Click .
#Text=It 's near the top of the profile menu .
#Text=It 's next to an icon that resembles a gear .
#Text=This opens the Creator Studio , which allows you to edit video .

#Text=If " YouTube Studio ( Beta ) " appears in your profile menu , instead of Creator Studio , click YouTube Studio ( Beta ) in the profile menu , and then click Creator Studio Classic in the sidebar to the left .
#Text=Sharing Private videos is not yet available in YouTube Studio .
#Text=Click .
#Text=It 's in the sidebar to the left .
#Text=This displays a list of all your uploaded videos .
#Text=Click below the video you want to share .
#Text=The edit button is below each video in the list .
#Text=This opens the Edit Video menu in Creator Studio .
#Text=Click .
#Text=It 's on the right side of the screen below the drop-down menu that says " Private " .
#Text=This displays a pop-up that allows you to add users you want to share the video with .
#Text=Type the email addresses of YouTube users .
#Text=Use the box to type the email address associated with any YouTube users you want to share the video with .
#Text=The user must have a YouTube account in order to be able to view a video set to private .
#Text=Click .
#Text=This sends an email invite to the user to notify them you have shared a video with them .
